<item>
            <title>[FLINK-12688] Make serializer lazy initialization thread safe in StateDescriptor</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-12688</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As per &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-11987?focusedCommentId=16832335&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-16832335&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;discussed&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-11987&quot; title=&quot;Kafka producer occasionally throws NullpointerException&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-11987&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-11987&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, this JIRA aims at resolving the issue of &lt;tt&gt;StateDescriptor#initializeSerializerUnlessSet&lt;/tt&gt; under race condition. More specified, we will assure no NPE thrown as well as the singleton of &lt;tt&gt;serializer&lt;/tt&gt; when invoking &lt;tt&gt;initializeSerializerUnlessSet&lt;/tt&gt; in parallel.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
